The paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It also involves optimization and decision-making (cs.DS), as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The use of dynamic programming and Markov mechanisms suggests a connection to control theory and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
